      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "dcfb2eea21c2e10d",
        "text": "Pastoralism: Pastoralism is the practice of raising livestock for livelihood. Azanya (1996) refers to pastoralism as an economy based on raising livestock which could be undertaken by sedentary or nomadic groups. Nomadism refers to the spatial movement of herdsmen. Nomadism and pastoralism are intertwined. Indeed, nomadism represents an integral, social, political and environment dimension of pastoralism. (Shettima & Tar: 2008; 165). "
      },
      "date": 1501618505340
    },
