        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "6d9280aed5a52f33",
        "text": "Conflict is a universal phenomenon because it occurs in all human societies in the world. It is an intrinsic and inevitable part of human existence (Francis, 2007). The term “conflict” derives from confligere, a Latin word which means “to strike together.” In its original context, conflict had a physical rather than a moral connotation (Albert, 2001). In his own opinion, Deutsch (1977) says that conflict is an action which prevents, obstructs, interferes with, injures or renders ineffective, another action with which it is incompatible. "
