      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "06804658f87b9541",
        "text": "A conflict situation arises when two or more parties perceive a threat to their needs, interests or concern. In other words, conflict is fuelled and exaggerated by people’s perception of a problem rather than reality. There is also the issue of perceptual filters which influences people’s reactions to a conflict.   Furthermore, in many conflict situations, there is usually a significant level of misunderstanding of each other’s perceptions, needs and feelings. To a Fulani herdsman, for instance, his greatest concern is the survival of his cattle and he cannot understand why anybody should frown at his efforts in feeding his animals."
