        "text": "(f) Greater internationalization of migration with pastoralists from neighbouring countries making long range movements to other countries for lush green pasture. In pre-colonial times, there were no legal boundaries among nation states, hence pastoralists moved freely and crossed borders in search of pasture. As Lattimore (1940;1962)  pointed  out, pastoral nomads are driven by the “sovereign importance of movement” and boundaries and territories have never had any meaning to them.  However, colonial masters created artificial boundaries which, in some cases, split ethnic groups into different countries. This situation compounded the problem of pastoralists."
