      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "87a5c670001b2211",
        "text": "There are different categories of Pastoralists. Some are nomadic, semi-settled (transhumant) and settled (sedentary agro pastoralists) according to the degree of mobility (Oladele and Oladele 2011). Albert (2012:105) categorized the Fulanis in Oke Ogun into four. The first is the Fulani Yorubas or the “Fulani Ile” i.e Fulanis who were born and bred in Oke Ogun or whose parents were born in Oke Ogun and they speak Yoruba and Fulfude languages fluently. The second type is the settled Fulani who have chosen to live in Oke Ogun and move their herds around the area in search of pasture. It was revealed that those familiar with Oke Ogun move their herds about carefully, without destroying crops and in the event of any destruction, willingly settle with the   farmers."
