        "text": "The third type of Fulanis, according to Albert, are the itinerant Fulanis who roam around with their herds and their families. They settle in one place for some time and later move,   especially in the dry season, in search of pasture .It is said that these group are also easier to relate with should their herds destroy farms. The last and the most dreaded are the ones called the Bororos who are young Fulanis hired to herd animals belonging to wealthy and influential people in Northern Nigeria. These are the ones that drive their herds into farms, destroying them with impunity. Since they carry dangerous weapons including guns, they attack the farmers and can maim or kill. Anyone who challenges them risks being assaulted or killed. Unverifiable information often allege that they partake in robberies either on the highways or in the bush and some times, maim or kill victims. "
